{"lemma": "قَصَبٌ", "slug": "قَصَبٌ", "root": "ق.ص.ب", "root_slug": "ق-ص-ب", "root_link": "/words/roots/ق-ص-ب", "pos": "N", "pos_camel": "noun", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": false}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 4, "pos_tags": ["noun", "verb"], "has_etymology": true, "sense_count": 7}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n35721"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%82%D9%8E%D8%B5%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%8C"}}, "translations": {"en": "reed", "fa": "نی", "ur": "نی", "tr": "kamış", "id": "tebu", "bn": "কঁকুড়", "es": "caña", "fr": "roseau", "de": "Rohr", "ru": "тростник", "zh": "芦苇"}, "definition": {"source": "wiktextract", "senses": [{"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to cut up (a slaughtered animal)"}, {"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to curl, carve"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "verbal noun of قَصَبَ (qaṣaba) (form I)", "tags": ["form-of", "noun-from-verb"]}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "stalk", "tags": ["collective"]}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "reed, cane (especially sugarcane)", "tags": ["collective"]}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "thread, filament", "tags": ["collective"], "examples": [{"text": "وفلسقيتان أُخريان من بِلّوْر مربّط ففضة، مذهّبة الناحية الواحدة، مشبكة بجواهر، وفي وسطها درات، وفي الناحية الأخُرَى أَربع قصبات فضة مطلية بذهب، وكرنيب وكوز فضة مطليّان بذهب مجرى فيهما الجوهر.", "english": "And two other flasks are of crystals twined with silver, gildened in one corner, netted with jewels, and in their mids pearls, and in the other corner four threads of silver thatched with gold, and a bowl and a mug of silver layered both with gold and woven with gemstones."}]}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "pipe", "tags": ["collective"]}]}, "etymology": {"source": "wiktextract", "text": "Back-formation from قَصَّاب (qaṣṣāb, “butcher”) borrowed from Aramaic קצבא / ܩܰܨܳܒܳܐ (qaṣṣābā), therewith forming a root ق ص ب (q ṣ b). Doublet of indigenous Arabic قَضَبَ (qaḍaba, “to cut off, to trim”).\n\nFrom the root ق ص ب (q ṣ b) of the aforementioned verb meaning “to be segment”, “to be cut into sections”, “to be severed”; stemming from a reed's divisions or from being collected as cut pieces; compare قَضْب (qaḍb)."}, "ipa": null, "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n35721", "headword_ar": "قَصَبٌ", "root": "qSb", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": "[a coll. gen. n., signifying"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Reeds,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "canes;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the like,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "culms"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of corn, &c.; and sometimes signifying"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a reed,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "cane,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the like,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a species thereof;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "any plant having"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M, A, Mgh, Msb, K)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "its stem composed of"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Mgh, Msb)"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^anaAbiyb", "text_ar": "اَنَابِيب"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "internodial portions"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] (M, A, Mgh, Msb, K)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "their"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kuEuwb", "text_ar": "كُعُوب"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "connecting knots,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "joints"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; (Mgh, Msb;) [i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "any kind,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "species, of plant having a jointed stem;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "i. q."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^abaA='N", "text_ar": "اَبَا=ءٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[a word comparatively little known]; (S; [in the O"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AanA'", "text_ar": "اَناء"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", a mistranscription;]) and [it is said that] ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaSobaA='u", "text_ar": "قَصْبَا=ءُ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "signifies the same: (S, O: [but see what follows:]) the n. un. of the former is ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaSabapN", "text_ar": "قَصَبَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, M, Mgh, Msb, K) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaSobaApN", "text_ar": "قَصْبَاةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaSabaApN", "text_ar": "قَصَبَاةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (K accord. to different copies; the former accord. to the TA: [but each of these I believe to be a mistake for ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaSuboA='apN", "text_ar": "قَصُبْا=ءَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", which is said to be a n. un. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaSobaA='u", "text_ar": "قَصْبَا=ءُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and therefore held by some to be syn. with"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaSabapN", "text_ar": "قَصَبَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ":]) ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaSobaA='u", "text_ar": "قَصْبَا=ءُ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[appears, however, to differ somewhat from"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaSab", "text_ar": "قَصَب"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", for it is said that it] signifies"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "an assemblage of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaSab", "text_ar": "قَصَب"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (M, K;) and its n. un. is ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaSabapN", "text_ar": "قَصَبَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaSobaA='apN", "text_ar": "قَصْبَا=ءَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[like"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HalafapN", "text_ar": "حَلَفَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HalofaA='apN", "text_ar": "حَلْفَا=ءَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "which are both said to be ns. un. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HalofaA='N", "text_ar": "حَلْفَا=ءٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "TarafapN", "text_ar": "طَرَفَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "TarofaA='apN", "text_ar": "طَرْفَا=ءَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", said to be ns. un. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "TarofaA='N", "text_ar": "طَرْفَا=ءٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; the former in each case anomalous]: (M: [see also Ham p. 201:]) or, accord. to Sb, ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaSobaA='u", "text_ar": "قَصْبَا=ءُ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is sing. and pl., (S, M, Mgh, O,) and so"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "TarofaA='u", "text_ar": "طَرْفَا=ءُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, M, O,) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HalofaA='u", "text_ar": "حَلْفَا=ءُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (S, O;) as pl. and as sing. also having the sign of the fem. gender; therefore, when they mean to express the sing. signification, they add the epithet"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "waAHidapN", "text_ar": "وَاحِدَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; thus, and thus only, distinguishing the sing. meaning from the pl., and making a difference between a word of this class and a noun that denotes a pl. meaning and has not the sign of the fem. gender such as"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "tamorN", "text_ar": "تَمْرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "busorN", "text_ar": "بُسْرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and such as"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aroTFY", "text_ar": "اَرْطًى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EaloqFY", "text_ar": "عَلْقًى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of which the ns. un. are"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aroTaApN", "text_ar": "اَرْطَاةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EaloqaApN", "text_ar": "عَلْقَاةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (M:) or, as some say, ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaSobaA='u", "text_ar": "قَصْبَا=ءُ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "signifies"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "many"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaSab", "text_ar": "قَصَب"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "growing in a place:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Mgh:) and it signifies also"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a place in which"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaSab", "text_ar": "قَصَب"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "grow:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M, K:) [or] ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maqoSabapN", "text_ar": "مَقْصَبَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "has this last meaning; (Mgh, Msb;) or signifies, like ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aroDN qaSibapN", "text_ar": "اَرْضٌ قَصِبَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ","}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a land having"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaSab", "text_ar": "قَصَب"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (M, K. *) ―         -b2-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aHoraza qaSaba", "text_ar": "اَحْرَزَ قَصَبَ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Als~aboqi", "text_ar": "السَّبْقِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Msb,) or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Als~aboqi", "text_ar": "السَّبْقِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaSabapa", "text_ar": "قَصَبَةَ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (TA,) [meaning (assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He won,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "acquired, the canes,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "cane, of victory in racing,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] is said of the winner in horseracing: they used to set up, in the horse-course, a cane ("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaSabap", "text_ar": "قَصَبَة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ",) and he who outstripped plucked it up and took it, in order that he might be known to be the one who outstripped, without contention: this was the origin of the phrase: then, in consequence of frequency of usage, it was applied also to the expeditious, quick, and light, or active: (Msb, * TA:) [accord. to the TA, it is a tropical phrase, but perhaps it is so only when used in the latter way:] it is said in a trad. of Sa'eed Ibn-El-Ás, that he measured the horse-course with the cane, making it to be a hundred canes in length, and the cane was stuck upright in the ground at the goal, and he who was first in arriving at it took it, and was entitled to the stake. (O, TA. [See also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "muqaS~ibN", "text_ar": "مُقَصِّبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".]) ―         -b3-  [The ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaSabap", "text_ar": "قَصَبَة", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "here mentioned as"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A certain measure of length,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "used in measuring race-courses, was also used in other cases, in measuring land, and differed in different countries and in different times: accord. to some, it was ten cubits; thus nearly agreeing with our “ rod: ” (see"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jariybN", "text_ar": "جَرِيبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ":) accord. to others, six cubits and a third of a cubit: (see"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fad~aAnN", "text_ar": "فَدَّانٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ":) the modern Egyptian"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaSabap", "text_ar": "قَصَبَة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", until it was reduced some years ago, was about twelve English feet and a half; its twentyfourth part, called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaboDapN", "text_ar": "قَبْضَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", being the measure of a man's fist with the thumb erect, or about six inches and a quarter.] ―         -b4-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlqaSabu AlfaArisiY~u", "text_ar": "القَصَبُ الفَارِسِىُّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The Persian reed"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "is a kind whereof writing-reeds are made:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Mgh, Msb:) and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "another kind thereof is hard and thick; and of this kind are made musical reeds,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "pipes; and with it houses,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "chambers, are roofed."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Msb) One says,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaSabu", "text_ar": "قَصَبُ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlxT~i A^anofa*u mino qaSabi AlxaT~i", "text_ar": "الخطِّ اَنْفَذُ مِنْ قَصَبِ الخَطِّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Writingreeds are more penetrating,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "effective, than the canes of El-Khatt"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(which are spears); i. e., words wound more than spears]. (A, TA.) ―         -b5-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaSabu Als~uk~ari", "text_ar": "قَصَبُ السُّكَّرِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is well-known [as meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The sugar-cane"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: (Msb:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "this is of three kinds; white and yellow and black: of the first and second, but not of the third, the juice"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of which sugar is made"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "is expressed; and this expressed juice is called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Easalu AlqaSabi", "text_ar": "عَسَلُ القَصَبِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (Mgh.) ―         -b6-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaSabu", "text_ar": "قَصَبُ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Al*~ariyrapi", "text_ar": "الذَّرِيرَةِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[is"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Calamus aromaticus;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "also called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaSabu", "text_ar": "قَصَبُ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlT~iybi", "text_ar": "الطِّيبِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]:"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a species thereof has the joints near together, and breaks into many fragments,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "splinters, and the internodial portions thereof are filled with a substance like spiders' webs: when chewed, it has an acrid taste, and it is aromatic"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Mgh, Msb)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "when brayed,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "powdered;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Mgh;)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and inclines to yellowness and whiteness."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Mgh, Msb. [See also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "*ariyrapN", "text_ar": "ذَرِيرَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "*r", "text_ar": "ذر"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".]) ―         -b7-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaSabN", "text_ar": "قَصَبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "also signifies (assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Any round and hollow bone"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or rather"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "bones"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; (S, O;) it is pl. [or rather a coll. gen. n.] of which ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaSabapN", "text_ar": "قَصَبَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is the sing. [or n. un,], this latter signifying"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "any bone containing marrow;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M, K;) thus called by way of comparison [to the reed, or cane]. (M.) ―         -b8-  And (tropical:)  The"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "bones of the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yadaAni", "text_ar": "يَدَانِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rijolaAni", "text_ar": "رِجْلَانِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "arms"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "legs,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "hands"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "feet,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "but here app. meaning the latter], (A, Msb,) and the like: (Msb:) [or] (assumed tropical:)  the ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "phalanges,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "bones of the fingers"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "toes;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M, K, * TA;) (tropical:)  the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "bones whereof there are three in each finger and two in the thumb"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the like in the feet"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; (A, TA;) and Zj says, the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "bones of the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aSaAbiE", "text_ar": "اَصَابِع"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "fingers"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "toes"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "which are also called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sulaAmaY", "text_ar": "سُلَامَى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (Msb in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "slm", "text_ar": "سلم"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ":) or, as some say, the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "portions between every two joints of the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aSaAbiE", "text_ar": "اَصَابِع"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (M, TA:) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlA^aSaAbiEi", "text_ar": "الاَصَابِعِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaSabapu", "text_ar": "قَصَبَةُ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaSabupu AlA_iSobaEi", "text_ar": "قَصَبُةُ الاـِصْبَعِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] signifies"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^anomalap", "text_ar": "اَنْمَلَة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[here perhaps meaning the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "ungual phalanx"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of the finger"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "toe."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Msb, TA.) ―         -b9-  And (assumed tropical:)  The"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "bones"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "veins"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of a wing. (MF.) ―         -b10-  [And (assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Quills:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "thus in the phrase"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "SaAra Alr~iy$u qaSabFA", "text_ar": "صَارَ الرِّيشُ قَصَبًا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", in the K, voce"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^anuwqN", "text_ar": "اَنُوقٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The feathers became quills:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "n. un. ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaSabapN", "text_ar": "قَصَبَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": see"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "SanamapN", "text_ar": "صَنَمَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".] ―         -b11-  And (tropical:)  [The"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "bronchi;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "branches of the windpipe;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M, K;) and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "outlets of the breath;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K;) [i. e.]"}, {"kin