 jacinths."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(IAar, O, K.) So in the saying, in a trad., (O, K,) related as uttered by Gabriel, (O,) [cited in the S app. as an ex. of the meaning next preceding"}, {"kind": "page_break", "n": 2530}, {"kind": "text", "text": "this last,]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ba$~iro xadiyjapa bibayoti fiY Aljan~api mino qaSabK", "text_ar": "بَشِّرْ خَدِيجَةَ بِبَيْتِ فِى الجَنَّةِ مِنْ قَصَبٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(IAar, O, K) i. e. ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Rejoice thou Khadeejeh by the announcement of"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a pavilion"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in Paradise"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of brilliant pearls,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "&c.: (IAar, O:) or the meaning is,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of hollow pearls"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "pearl"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "],"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "spacious, like the lofty palace:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(IAth, TA:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of emerald:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA voce"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bayotN", "text_ar": "بَيْتٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ":) and it is said by some to convey an allusion to Khadeejeh's acquiring what is termed"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaSabu Als~aboqi", "text_ar": "قَصَبُ السَّبْقِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[expl. above], because she was the first person, or the first of women, who embraced El-Islám. (MF, TA.) ―         -b14-  And (tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Fine, thin,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "delicate,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, O,) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "soft,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M, Msb, K,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "garments,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "cloths, of linen:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, M, O, Msb, K:) a single one thereof is called ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaSabiY~N", "text_ar": "قَصَبِىٌّ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (M, O, Msb, K.) One says,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maEa fulaAnK qaSabu SanoEaA='a", "text_ar": "مَعَ فُلَانٍ قَصَبُ صَنْعَا=ءَ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "waqaSabu miSora", "text_ar": "وَقَصَبُ مِصْرَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(tropical:)  ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "In the possession of such a one are"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaSab", "text_ar": "قَصَب"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the cylindrical,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "oblong, hollow pieces"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of carnelian"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of San'à"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "],"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaSab", "text_ar": "قَصَب"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the fine,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "soft, garments,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "cloths,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of linen"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of Egypt"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (A.) ―         -b15-  Also (tropical:)  The"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "channels by which water flows from the springs,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "sources:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, M, A, O, K:) or the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "channels by which the water of a well flows from the springs,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "sources:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(As, T, TA:) n. un. ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaSabapN", "text_ar": "قَصَبَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (M.) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaSabu", "text_ar": "قَصَبُ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlbaToHaA='i", "text_ar": "البَطْحَا=ءِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The waters"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of the kind of water-course called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bTHA='", "text_ar": "بطحا=ء"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(q. v.)]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "that run to the springs,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "sources, of the wells."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(As, S, O.) Aboo-Dhueyb says,"}, {"kind": "quote", "text": "A^aqaAmato bihi faA@botanato xayomapF\n                      \n                     \n                        EalaY qaSabK wafuraAtK naharo"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(As, S, M, O,) meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "She remained"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in it, and constructed"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "for herself"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a booth,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a tent,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "amid wells and sweet water that flowed copiously."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(As, S, O.) ―         -b16-  See also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaSabapN", "text_ar": "قَصَبَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "below, in the next paragraph.       -A2-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlqaSabu", "text_ar": "القَصَبُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is also a name for"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The ewe."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(O.) ―         -b2-  And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaSabo qaSabo", "text_ar": "قَصَبْ قَصَبْ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A call to the ewe"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(O, K)"}, {"kind": "ita